                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.102 S/234: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cunningham</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-04-16T18:00:00+08:00"
                            >April 16, 1930—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 16—10:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Following telegram has been sent to the Legation: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>April 16, 6 p.m. The Shanghai Municipal Council presented a resolution to
                            the annual ratepayers’ meeting today proposing the increase in the
                            Chinese members of the Council from 3 to 5. The resolution was
                            vigorously opposed by MacDonald, a prominent British ratepayer.
                            Prominent among his reasons for opposing the resolution was the fact
                            that the resolution had been proposed by the Council under pressure. The
                            chairman stated that no influence whatsoever was used toward the Council
                            and that the resolution represented the views of the foreign members of
                            the Council. When the vote was reached the resolution was defeated by a
                            large majority. Repeated to the Department.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cunningham</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
